obo:ECO_0007695  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_302  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this study, Rizzoli et al. showed that synaptosomal endocytic vesicles have the ability to fuse to PC12-cell acceptor endosomes. And the fusion predominantly depends on endosomal SNAREs, such as Syntaxin 6 and Vamp4. In order to show that this fusion is specifically mediated by endosomal SNARES and not exocytotic SNAREs, they added recombinant SNARE proteins to the fusion reactions. The result revealed that synaptobrevin 2 and combination of SNAP 25/syntaxin does not block the fusion; however, VAMP4 and a combination of vti1a, syntaxin 6 and syntaxin 13 significantly inhibited the reaction.. Experimental description: PC12 cells (clone 251) were grown in DMEM with the following additions (v/v): 5% fetal calf serum, 10% horse serum, 4 mM glutamine, 100 U/mL penicillin/streptomycin. Cells were grown to 80% confluence at 378Cin 10% CO2.BHK-21 cells were cultured in similar medium (with 10% tryptasephosphate instead of horse serum).\n\n5/2/2018 Pim\n- Overexpressed Vamp4 is of rat species: \"Rat VAMP4 (1-117) pGEX-KG was provided by W. Antonin.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_302" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

